Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph wikg://local/job

Purpose:
  Manage device-local generation tasks for `.wikg` chapters.

Usage:
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input <chapter-uri|archive-uri> --task <reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph> --accept-cost [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]
  wikigraph wikg://local/job list [--all] [--active] [--input <archive-uri>]
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> get [--json]
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> watch [--jsonl] [--from beginning|now]
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> pause
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> resume
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> cancel
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> boost
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id>/target set <reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph>
  wikigraph wikg://local/job clean

Tasks:
  - reading-graph builds the reading-oriented chunk graph from sourced text.
  - reading-summary builds summaries from the Reading Graph. It builds reading-graph first when needed.
  - knowledge-graph builds entity mentions from sourced text. Use this before searching an entity lens such as `<archive-uri>/entity`.

Task shape:
  - reading-graph -> reading-summary is the Reading Graph line.
  - Queueing reading-summary while reading-graph is already active for the same chapter upgrades the same Reading Graph-line job.
  - Queueing reading-graph while reading-summary is already active keeps the reading-summary job, because it already includes reading-graph.
  - knowledge-graph is a separate lane. It can be active for the same chapter while the Reading Graph line is active.
  - Source is not generated by the queue. A planned chapter must receive source text before any queue task can start.

Cost:
  Queue tasks may call an LLM, consume tokens, and incur provider charges.
  `wikg://local/job add` requires `--accept-cost`.

Examples:
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3 --task reading-graph --accept-cost
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input wikg://book.wikg --task knowledge-graph --accept-cost
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3 --task reading-summary --accept-cost
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3 --task knowledge-graph --accept-cost
  wikigraph wikg://local/job list --input wikg://book.wikg --json
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> watch --jsonl
